SST and Chl-a Regional Summaries

March 06, 2023

Below are monthly time series of mean sea surface temperature (SST, \(^\circ\)C) and chlorophyll-a concentration (Chla, mg m-3) for regions and stations of interest, including Marine Protected Areas (MPAs). Click on the tabs to view plots.

The SST is a 4km resolution product available from NOAA, covering late 1981 to 2022. The remainder of 2022 was supplemented with SST from the NASA Ocean Biology Processing Group (OBPG). The Chla is a 4km product available from the NASA OBPG covering 2003 to present.

The time series are coloured by season: winter (January, February, March), spring (April, May, June), summer (July, August, September), and autumn (October, November, December).

Click here to view map


Regions and Sites of Interest (indicated in orange):

  • EHV: Endeavour Hydrothermal Vents MPA
  • GH: East (GHE), Offshore (GHO), South (GHS), West (GHW) Gwaii Haanas National Park Reserve, National Marine Conservation Area Reserve, and Haida Heritage Site
  • SI: Scott Islands marine National Wildlife Area
  • SK-B: SGaan Kinghlas-Bowie Seamount MPA
  • SR: Central (SRC), North (SRN), South (SRS) Hecate Strait/Queen Charlotte Sound Glass Sponge Reefs MPA
  • TḥT: Tang.ɢwan – ḥačxwiqak – Tsig̱is MPA
  • A1, BARK, E01, GI02, Mason53, P4, Q19 standard oceanographic stations: the statistics used are from a 5x5 pixel box centered at the station coordinates
